title: Grateful Dead Live at The Centrum on 1983-10-20
lineage: Senn 441s (FOB) > PCM > DAT > CDRx? > EAC > SF 6.0 > CD Wave > SHN
description: Bertha-> Greatest Story Ever Told, West L.A. Fadeaway, Minglewood Blues, Tennessee Jed, Hell In A Bucket, Row Jimmy, Looks Like Rain-> Deal Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower-> Samson & Delilah-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Spanish Jam-> The Other One-> Stella Blue-> Around & Around-> Good Lovin', E: Day Job

reviews.review_text:
Silberman's 10-21-83 One of the finest audience recordings I have ever heard. Posterity's sake makes the violation of taping rules excusable.

This show is worth it for just the 30-minute scarlet/Fire alone, but a nice Wharf Rat, a rocking Miracle, a Music opener, among others make it a must have.
hmmmm Second set marred by vocal meltdowns from what I can hear...oh Jerrry...namely Stella Blue.

Cant win for tryin'........................ Very crisp AUD. recording...The Centrum became a must-see venue after this show...Check out Stella...Jerry fucks up the opening verse,,,All the years........Bobby was yelling  'combine'......Jerry said  'fuck it', and just kept jamming....by the time we got to every blue light cheap hotel...we were vindicated...awesome show..Great parking lot scene before the show....You just cant party like that anymore..I miss those days.....

First ever Centrum Dead show This show was the first ever Dead show at the newly opened Worcester Centrum, so yes it did become a must see venue after that ;-) I made it a point to never miss a dead show if I could get to it after this one!

He Nodded Off !! The Fat man nodded off between The Other One and Stella. Bobby went and tapped Jerry on the shoulder.True !!! Bobby repeated a similar stunt pulling Dylans cord during Baby Blue at RFK in 86!
